		<td><b>Dual Language FFV?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'm trying to turn a retail cart of FFV into a switchable dual-language cartridge by leaving the cart in normal shape and soldering a TSOP package under one of the existing mask roms.<br /><br />Now, I know I need a decoder to make this work, as the cart (SHVC-2J3B-01) has 2 mask rom slots, sram, and a built-in 74LS139 and 74LS00.<br /><br />Is there any way to use these built in decoders, or will I need to add an additional 74LS139 and tie it to the 74LS00 and switch the original mask rom lines on/off when I want it in english?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


