	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Dual Language FFV?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">DNSDies wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm trying to turn a retail cart of FFV into a switchable dual-language cartridge by leaving the cart in normal shape and soldering a TSOP package under one of the existing mask roms.<br /><br />Now, I know I need a decoder to make this work, as the cart (SHVC-2J3B-01) has 2 mask rom slots, sram, and a built-in 74LS139 and 74LS00.<br /><br />Is there any way to use these built in decoders, or will I need to add an additional 74LS139 and tie it to the 74LS00 and switch the original mask rom lines on/off when I want it in english?</div><br /><br /><br />I would think that you could double the roms and just tie your switch to the CE (chip enable) lines to select between the 2 versions.  No additional decoder's would be needed.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
